f its work of fracture wF (of uncut specimen) and P.\n(8) The elusive fractocohesive length Lfc defined in the literature as G_Ic/w_F\nnaturally arises from the new expression for G_Ic as stated in (7), i.e., it is\nessentially P. These results suggest that a great deal of future work is\nrequired to acquire additional understanding with regards to fracture and\nfailure behaviors of plastics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Nov 2021 18:05:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Nov 2021 22:06:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 5 Dec 2021 14:22:55 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 7 Dec 2021 17:59:43 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 9 Dec 2021 23:08:55 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 17 Dec 2021 15:37:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-02"}
