{"id":"2111.13320","submitter":"Mitia Duerinckx","authors":"Mitia Duerinckx and Raphael Winter","title":"Well-posedness of the Lenard-Balescu equation with smooth interactions","comments":"46 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The Lenard-Balescu equation was formally derived in the 1960s as the\nfundamental description of the collisional process in a spatially homogeneous\nsystem of interacting particles. It can be viewed as correcting the standard\nLandau equation by taking into account collective screening effects. Due to the\nreputed complexity of the Lenard-Balescu equation in case of Coulomb\ninteractions, its mathematical theory has remained void apart from the\nlinearized setting. In this contribution, we focus on the case of smooth\ninteractions and we show that dynamical screening effects can then be handled\nperturbatively. Taking inspiration from the Landau theory, we establish global\nwell-posedness close to equilibrium, local well-posedness away from\nequilibrium, and we discuss the convergence to equilibrium and the validity of\nthe Landau approximation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Nov 2021 05:53:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-29"}
